<topic id = "id131JK000M30"
    xmlns:ditaarch = "http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/">
<title>Rename Conditions</title>
<shortdesc>Renames conditions in the current file or book.</shortdesc>
<prolog><author>Scott Prentice</author>
<critdates><created date = "2013-01-19"/>
<revised modified = "2013-08-04"/></critdates></prolog>
<body><p><indexterm>conditions<indexterm>renaming</indexterm></indexterm>This
command requires setup to the RenameCondMap section of the <filepath>fm2dita.ini</filepath> file.
Once this INI section is updated with oldname/newname pairs, run
it on a file or book to rename the conditions in all files.</p>
<p>The <cmdname conref = "_shared.xml#id131KC0I0VHS/cmd_ren-conds"></cmdname> command
should be used to clean up condition naming before using the <cmdname
conref = "_shared.xml#id131KC0I0VHS/cmd_cond-to-attr"></cmdname> command.
It is always best to use the <cmdname conref = "_shared.xml#id131KC0I0VHS/cmd_show-conds"></cmdname> command
before using this command.</p></body></topic>
